article.headline: Marshall 72, East Carolina 66
article.story: HUNTINGTON, W.Va. (AP) --Mark Patton scored 17 points to lead Marshall to a 72-66 win over East Carolina on Wednesday. Markel Humphrey was the only other player scoring in double figures for Marshall (9-10, 2-4 C-USA). Humphrey scored 10 of his 11 points in the first half. East Carolina (7-13, 1-6) got 15 points apiece from Jeremy Ingram and Corey Rouse, who also grabbed nine rebounds. The victory halted Marshall's four-game conference losing streak and a three-game home losing streak. East Carolina lost its sixth straight road contest. The Pirates went on a 7-2 run to draw within three points, 69-66, with 31 seconds remaining, but Patton hit a pair of free-throws with 11 seconds left to seal the victory. Marshall shot 49 percent from the floor but went the last 3:41 without a field goal. The Thundering Herd never trailed over the final 37 minutes of play, but East Carolina tied the game at 36-36 early in the second half on Courtney Captain's pair of consecutive 3-pointers as part of an 8-0 run. Mark Dorris hit a layup to give Marshall the lead for good. After East Carolina scored the first five points of the game, Marshall reeled off a 19-4 run and took a 33-28 lead at halftime.<
